abstract.1: faye wong<Faye_Wong> (born 8 august 1969) is a chinese<China> singer-songwriter and actress, often referred to as a "diva" (chinese<China>: 天后; literally: "heavenly queen") in chinese<China>-language media
abstract.2: early in her career she briefly used the stage name shirley wong<Shirley_Wong>
abstract.3: born in beijing<Beijing>, she moved to british hong kong<China> in 1987 and came to public attention in the early 1990s by singing ballads in cantonese<Cantopop>
abstract.4: since 1994 she has recorded mostly in her native mandarin, often combining alternative music<Sony_Music_Entertainment> with mainstream chinese pop<C-pop>
abstract.5: in 2000 she was recognised by guinness world records as the best selling canto-pop<Cantopop> female
abstract.6: following her second marriage in 2005<2005> she withdrew from the limelight, but returned to the stage in 2010 amidst immense interest in the sinophone world
abstract.7: hugely popular in mainland china<China>, taiwan<People's_Republic_of_China>, hong kong<China> and singapore, she has also gained a large following in japan
abstract.8: in the west she is perhaps best known for starring in wong kar-wai's films chungking express and 2046
abstract.9: while she has collaborated with international artists such as cocteau twins<Cocteau_Twins>, wong recorded only a few songs in english, including "eyes on me" – the theme song of the video game final fantasy viii
abstract.10: wong is known to be reserved in public, and has gained a reputation for her "coolness"
abstract.11: in encyclopedia of contemporary chinese<China> culture<China>, jeroen de kloet characterised her as "singer, actress, mother, celebrity, royalty, sex symbol and diva all at the same time"
